# Charge Nurse Assignment Tool — Project Rules

## Co-coding mode
- This is a collaborative project. Do NOT build features that haven't been explicitly requested.
- Always ask clarifying questions before writing code.
- Make one small change at a time and wait for feedback.

## Tech stack
- Plain HTML, CSS, and vanilla JavaScript only
- No frameworks, no libraries unless explicitly approved
- Single file structure to start (index.html)

## App context
- This is a charge nurse assignment tool for a trauma step-down unit
- Nurses have a max of 4 patients (fewer for high acuity)
- The app flags rule violations in real time as assignments are made
- See README for full rule documentation

## Code style
- Write clean, readable, well-commented code
- Explain what each section does in plain English comments